        <div class="denomination-strip">

            <h4>Cathcart Church of Scotland and Cathcart United Free Church Covenant (2026)</h4>

            <p>The congregations of Cathcart Church of Scotland and Cathcart United Free
            Church of Scotland share a common faith and calling.</p>

            <p>We believe in one God &mdash; Father, Son and Holy Spirit &mdash; and share
            in the calling to serve God's purposes in the world.</p>

            <p>We recognise and affirm the uniqueness of the congregations and the importance
            of working together.</p>

            <h4>We're committed to:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Proclaiming the Kingdom of God</li>
                <li>Declaring the gospel of Jesus Christ</li>
                <li>Sharing in the work God has called us to do</li>
                <li>Growing together in faith</li>
                <li>Serving our communities in the love and strength of Christ</li>
                <li>Providing opportunities for all to grow in knowledge and understanding
                of faith and encouraging the living out of that faith</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>We agree:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide opportunities to worship, witness and serve together</li>
                <li>To pray and study God's Word jointly and separately</li>
                <li>To share resources of people and buildings</li>
                <li>To work with other congregations when that is possible</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>We will:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Share the preaching and teaching resources between the congregations</li>
                <li>Have good communication between the congregations</li>
                <li>Have joint working wherever feasible and beneficial</li>
                <li>Encourage supportive relationships across the congregations</li>
                <li>Seek God's will for the congregations jointly and separately</li>
                <li>Connect with the local community and be a blessing to it</li>
            </ul>

            <p>We agree to joint representation on the nominating/selection committee when
            a new minister is sought by either congregation. Unless otherwise agreed, at
            least 2 members will be nominated from the 'other' congregation.</p>

            <p>We give thanks to God for bringing us together in faith, worship and service
            and seek His way forward in this covenant relationship.</p>

            <h4>Signed 1 February 2026</h4>
            <p>
                Alasdair MacMillan <em>(Minister, Cathcart Church of Scotland)</em><br />
                John Fulton <em>(Interim Moderator, Cathcart United Free Church)</em><br />
                Ewan Gourlay <em>(Session Clerk, Cathcart Church of Scotland)</em><br />
                Lesley Mathieson <em>(Session Clerk, Cathcart United Free Church)</em>
            </p>

        </div>

